# Button Usage

For primary actions, always use `<Button variant="default">`.

For secondary actions, use only `secondary`, `outline`, or `ghost`.

If a button must not be color-filled, use `variant="outline"` or `variant="ghost"`, not `default` or `neutral`.

Never add local color classes to buttons (`text-blue-*`, `bg-blue-*`, `border-blue-*`, `text-indigo-*`, `bg-sky-*`, etc.).

Do not invent custom visual variants for new pages; use existing `ui/button` variants tied to theme tokens.
